The paper discusses machine learning algorithms for decision-making and control policies, specifically in the context of Imitation Learning (IL). This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the algorithms on simulated continuous control domains, which suggests relevance to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of state distributions, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV) if the state is represented visually.
